# Communication style

When writing explanations, documentation, or user-facing text in this project:

- Avoid abbreviations when they might be unclear. When you use one, spell it out the first time or add a short gloss (for example: "content delivery network (CDN)").
- Common technology terms that most developers recognize without explanation are fine to use as-is (examples: API, HTML, CSS, URL, HTTP).

This keeps answers readable for humans who do not share the same shorthand.
